<emphasis box="[382,596,1078,1102]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Chiomara crenda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[603,757,1078,1102]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1440,1126,1345]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1126,1150]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus without close relatives (
<figureCitation box="[734,804,1126,1150]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="16.[192,275,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,214,1144]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[192,1440,213,1144]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 6. Genomic trees of Erynnini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677247/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Keys to F. 
<quantity box="[942,1027,1126,1150]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.429" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="in" value="13.5">13.5 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1032,1191,1126,1150]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
who gives a detailed diagnosis. Importantly, genitalia (except saccus and penis) are close to symmetrical, especially the uncus. Both uncus and valvae are highly asymmetrical in 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1899" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1899" box="[927,1384,1191,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Chiomara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1050,1191,1215]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Chiomara</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1899
</taxonomicName>
and other related genera such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1896" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[560,1024,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Theagenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[560,687,1223,1247]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Theagenes</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1896" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gorgythion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1038,1175,1223,1247]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Gorgythion</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1896
</taxonomicName>
. Symmetrical uncus with a pair of side processes on each side at its base, diagnostic of the genus. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly318.44.1:C664A, aly114.5.7:A142T, aly114.5.7:G143C, aly1294.17.1:A1681C, aly536.188.2:G103C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
